snippet.textDisplay: Play Southern Columbia almost yearly in different sports. Very good athletes who excel especially in football and wrestling. Always fun to lose by a billion points lol.  Although they recruit kids and they push the age limits of eligibility. So what your seeing is 20 yo’s playing against 14-17 yo’s.  Some of these highlights are from district playoffs this year and the kids that had already signed to division I schools were basically off limits. No risking injuries to those kids when your gonna lose by 100 points anyways.  No need to blame kids it’s the system that’s been allowed to happen. The kids are great kids without attitudes and it’s always fun to watch them as they progress through college.
